John R. Cumpson https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/John_R._Cumpson 0 John R. Cumpson (August 30, 1866-March 15, 1913) was an American film and stage actor. He appeared in 124 films between 1905 and 1912. A 1910 newspaper item described Cumpson as "the famous Swedish dialect comedian."On Broadway, Cumpson appeared in Up York State (1901).Cumpson died of pneumonia and diabetes at Washington Heights Hospital in New York City. He was survived by a brother and two sisters. John_R._Cumpson ( August_30 , 1866-March_15_,_1913 ) was an_American_film_and_stage_actor . He appeared in 124_films between 1905_and_1912 .
